A struct can be used to create custom data types.
Ex: 

struct xyf {
	x:u32
	y:i32
	flag:bool
}

You can also assign valued to variables in the structure like this:

struct Template {
    x:u32,
    y:i32,
    flag:bool
}

fn main () {
    let temp = Template{
        x:23,
        y:-34,
        flag:true
    };

println!("{}", temp.flag);

}

Here we are creating a variable inside the main function using the the struct.
Then we are assigning values to all the variables inside the struct from the variable
